WEBVTT

00:00.081 --> 00:01.462
[Voiceover]
Previously on "Nashville..."

00:01.462 --> 00:02.713
- This is Randall St. Clair.

00:02.713 --> 00:04.335
He'll be
our new social media

00:04.335 --> 00:05.886
and digital marketing man.

00:05.886 --> 00:07.428
- Ms. Jaymes,
I'm your biggest fan.

00:09.180 --> 00:11.892
- You sold it to Google
for $2 billion?

00:11.892 --> 00:13.184
- Zach Welles.
- Hi.

00:13.184 --> 00:14.595
- I had the idiotic notion

00:14.595 --> 00:15.896
that I could do something
in the music business.

00:15.896 --> 00:17.098
I was hoping
we could meet up.

00:17.098 --> 00:18.769
- We got to look
for a place together.

00:18.769 --> 00:20.941
- The keep telling you
to be patient.

00:20.941 --> 00:22.943
- I'm sick of being patient.

00:22.943 --> 00:25.106
I'm never gonna get better.
- Don't say that.

00:25.106 --> 00:28.739
- She just peed on my legs,
and I felt it.

00:30.611 --> 00:34.115
- (groans)

00:36.207 --> 00:39.710
You can go further.
I can take it. Aah!

00:39.710 --> 00:42.503
- Okay.
(baby fusses)

00:42.503 --> 00:44.625
- It's okay, baby.
Mama's all right.

00:44.625 --> 00:46.217
-I got her.
Come here, baby girl.

00:46.217 --> 00:47.428
- Did you remember
to take your oxycodone

00:47.428 --> 00:48.669
before we started
this morning?

00:51.132 --> 00:53.804
- Oh, right.

00:53.804 --> 00:55.846
- We can't do our best work

00:55.846 --> 00:56.937
if you're in too much pain.

00:56.937 --> 00:59.770
- I'm not. I swear.

00:59.770 --> 01:03.444
I think I could do something
even more advanced.

01:03.444 --> 01:04.645
- Maybe next session.

01:04.645 --> 01:08.899
- I just feel like
I'm lying here

01:08.899 --> 01:10.991
all the time like a lump.
- I know it's frustrating.

01:10.991 --> 01:13.994
But you got to crawl
before you can walk.

01:13.994 --> 01:16.117
Not literally.
- Good.

01:16.117 --> 01:17.998
- You just
regained sensation.

01:17.998 --> 01:19.460
You can't put any weight
on this

01:19.460 --> 01:20.871
until the fixator comes off.

01:20.871 --> 01:23.414
- Okay, but I saw
something online.

01:23.414 --> 01:27.878
There's a device
that they put people in

01:27.878 --> 01:30.421
where they can walk without
gravity or something like that?

01:30.421 --> 01:32.423
- It's not exactly
without gravity.

01:32.423 --> 01:35.556
You're thinking of a device
that redistributes weight.

01:35.556 --> 01:37.558
- I don't care!
Just get me in one!

01:39.059 --> 01:44.064
I mean,
I would appreciate

01:44.064 --> 01:47.278
if I could try it out.

01:47.278 --> 01:49.650
- The clinic does have one,
but it's really for patients

01:49.650 --> 01:51.071
who are further along
in their recovery.

01:51.071 --> 01:53.734
- How much further along?

01:53.734 --> 01:55.406
- Let's just focus on
where you're at right now.

01:55.406 --> 01:57.117
- Yeah.

01:59.500 --> 02:02.953
- I think I found it.
- Huh?

02:02.953 --> 02:04.665
- I just came from
a place on Greenwood.

02:04.665 --> 02:06.126
It's gorgeous in person.

02:06.126 --> 02:09.340
- Is that the one
with the gym?

02:09.340 --> 02:11.302
- No, that's the big complex
near Hadley Park.

02:11.302 --> 02:13.594
But we crossed that
off the list.

02:13.594 --> 02:16.136
I thought we agreed we didn't
want to be that far west.

02:16.136 --> 02:17.808
- Oh, right.

02:17.808 --> 02:19.139
- You're gonna love it.

02:19.139 --> 02:21.061
I made an appointment
to go back on Friday.

02:21.061 --> 02:23.604
Hey, don't go back to sleep.
- (groans)

02:23.604 --> 02:25.065
- What, were you up partying
all night?

02:25.065 --> 02:28.689
- No. I had a gig.

02:28.689 --> 02:32.233
- Well,
why didn't you tell me?

02:32.233 --> 02:35.115
- You don't have to come
to every show I play.

02:35.115 --> 02:36.487
- What if I want to?

02:36.487 --> 02:38.199
- You hate those loud clubs.

02:38.199 --> 02:42.453
- I don't hate them.
I just don't like them.

02:42.453 --> 02:44.285
- I figured it'd be better

02:44.285 --> 02:47.628
if we spend time
doing things we both enjoy.

02:47.628 --> 02:49.920
- Like what?

02:49.920 --> 02:51.342
(knock on door)

02:51.342 --> 02:53.634
- Hey, Will,
you seen my keys?

02:53.634 --> 02:55.256
- No!

02:57.428 --> 02:59.850
- I can't wait for you
to get out of here.

03:03.894 --> 03:06.897
♪ Maybe I'll move
to California ♪

03:06.897 --> 03:11.232
♪ With the unbroken part of
my heart I still have left ♪

03:11.232 --> 03:14.615
♪ Maybe I'll fall in love
again someday ♪

03:14.615 --> 03:18.949
♪ I'm not gonna
hold my breath ♪

03:18.949 --> 03:22.453
♪ I'm not gonna
hold my breath ♪

03:22.453 --> 03:23.784
♪ I'm not-- ♪

03:23.784 --> 03:25.165
- See, that's just
so beautiful.

03:25.165 --> 03:27.668
- I know. We can't
afford her, though.

03:27.668 --> 03:29.290
- I know. We can't afford

03:29.290 --> 03:31.712
the first 10 directors
on our list.

03:31.712 --> 03:32.883
Hey, Randall?

03:32.883 --> 03:34.965
- Yes?
- Hey, I just wanted to say

03:34.965 --> 03:37.097
I love what you did
with the Exes' site,

03:37.097 --> 03:39.550
all the graphics and everything
on the new single.

03:39.550 --> 03:41.221
It's so cool.

03:41.221 --> 03:43.514
- Oh, my gosh.
Thank you.

03:43.514 --> 03:45.686
- Yeah.
Keep up the good work.

03:45.686 --> 03:49.149
- Absolutely. I will.

03:49.149 --> 03:51.812
- He just seems
terrified of me.

03:51.812 --> 03:54.525
- I think he's just
eager to please.

03:54.525 --> 03:56.567
- Oh, I don't know.
I can't watch these anymore.

03:56.567 --> 03:57.818
It's too depressing.

03:57.818 --> 03:59.530
- I mean,
what do you want to do?

03:59.530 --> 04:01.071
You want to tell Scarlett
and Gunnar we can't do a video?

04:01.071 --> 04:03.364
- No. I mean,
I think we keep looking.

04:03.364 --> 04:06.867
We'll find somebody who's young
and hungry and cheap.

04:06.867 --> 04:09.079
Oh, by the way, I'm gonna see
Scarlett and Gunnar

04:09.079 --> 04:10.371
this weekend
at the Bluebird.

04:10.371 --> 04:12.503
With Zach Welles,
incidentally.

04:12.503 --> 04:14.084
- Oh, your new best friend.

04:14.084 --> 04:16.337
- Well, you know all my best
friends are billionaires.

04:16.337 --> 04:17.798
- (chuckles)
Why don't you ask him

04:17.798 --> 04:19.139
if he's got 100 grand
laying around someplace

04:19.139 --> 04:21.091
he wouldn't mind us
using on the video?

04:21.091 --> 04:23.223
- Yeah.

04:23.223 --> 04:26.226
- Why would you tell someone
they're not ready?

04:26.226 --> 04:29.149
Isn't it her job
to be encouraging?

04:29.149 --> 04:30.851
- I'm sure she didn't
mean it that way.

04:30.851 --> 04:33.233
- I should call Tom Ericson.
- Who?

04:33.233 --> 04:34.695
- The medical director

04:34.695 --> 04:36.777
who asked me to send
the poster for his daughter.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.489
He runs the whole place.

04:38.489 --> 04:41.662
- You sure you want
to go over her head?

04:41.662 --> 04:43.574
- You don't have to do that.

04:43.574 --> 04:46.036
- I'm not doing anything.

04:46.036 --> 04:49.370
- No. I mean
cut the crust off.

04:49.370 --> 04:53.123
- Oh. Well, I know that's
how you like it, so...

04:53.123 --> 04:55.295
- But, really, it's fine.

04:55.295 --> 04:58.339
- Okay. Better eat fast.

04:58.339 --> 05:01.181
Emily's coming by
to drive you to psych.

05:02.683 --> 05:04.184
- I canceled my appointment.

05:05.686 --> 05:08.098
All the shrink wants
to talk about is the crash.

05:08.098 --> 05:10.230
I don't feel like
reliving it every week.

05:10.230 --> 05:11.602
- Yeah, but you can't
just not go.

05:11.602 --> 05:13.394
I mean, it's your treatment.

05:13.394 --> 05:15.195
- Well, shouldn't I have
some say over my treatment?

05:15.195 --> 05:16.987
- Of course.

05:16.987 --> 05:20.280
- Okay, well, I'd like to spend
the little energy that I have

05:20.280 --> 05:21.742
on things
that are more important.

05:21.742 --> 05:23.534
Like getting
out of that chair.

05:23.534 --> 05:26.707
- Right. Sorry.

05:26.707 --> 05:27.948
- What?

05:29.540 --> 05:30.791
- What?

05:30.791 --> 05:32.623
- You have a look
on your face.

05:32.623 --> 05:35.255
- This is just my face.

05:35.255 --> 05:38.088
- Oh. I guess
I never noticed.

05:38.088 --> 05:41.011
- I'm gonna go
check on Cadence.

05:51.522 --> 05:53.063
(groans)

06:24.465 --> 06:27.968
- Tell me again why we gotta
wine and dine this dude.

06:27.968 --> 06:29.349
- Well, we don't have to,

06:29.349 --> 06:31.512
but, you know,
he's in Nashville,

06:31.512 --> 06:33.724
and he's interested in
the country music business.

06:33.724 --> 06:35.686
- Or is he interested
in you?

06:35.686 --> 06:37.978
- Oh, please.
He's 12 years old,

06:37.978 --> 06:39.780
and I've made it very clear

06:39.780 --> 06:42.112
that you and I together
are taking him out.

06:42.112 --> 06:43.864
- Seems like
he's a little odd.

06:43.864 --> 06:46.487
In all these articles, they talk
about the off-beat entrepreneur,

06:46.487 --> 06:48.078
like that's his thing
or something.

06:48.078 --> 06:49.660
- Well,
it's probably accurate.

06:49.660 --> 06:51.702
You know, he's a nice guy.

06:51.702 --> 06:54.875
Seems smart.
I don't know.

06:54.875 --> 06:56.376
- I don't know what?

06:56.376 --> 07:01.882
- He is a big fan
and he's got a lot of money.

07:01.882 --> 07:03.003
- You're thinking maybe
he'll be able to help

07:03.003 --> 07:04.094
the company a little bit.

07:04.094 --> 07:08.098
- I think that
sometimes, yes.

07:08.098 --> 07:10.180
And then I think
it's guys like him

07:10.180 --> 07:11.852
and the whole digital world

07:11.852 --> 07:13.514
that have screwed up
the country music business

07:13.514 --> 07:14.725
in the first place.

07:14.725 --> 07:17.357
- Then you think
about the money again.

07:17.357 --> 07:20.060
- Shut up.
- (laughs)

07:23.524 --> 07:25.025
- Kevin, it's 10 A.M.

07:25.025 --> 07:26.987
I'm here.
Where are you?

07:26.987 --> 07:28.949
- I'm so sorry.
I got called in to work

07:28.949 --> 07:30.741
on that song
with Kacey Musgraves.

07:30.741 --> 07:32.202
- Well, should I reschedule?

07:32.202 --> 07:34.535
- No, no. You go.
I've already seen it.

07:34.535 --> 07:35.956
- Okay.

07:35.956 --> 07:40.290
- Oh, and I told the guy
that we were roommates.

07:40.290 --> 07:41.882
- What?

07:41.882 --> 07:43.714
- You never know what
peoples' biases are gonna be.

07:43.714 --> 07:45.756
They can decide not to rent
to you for any reason,

07:45.756 --> 07:47.718
and I didn't want
to give them one.

07:47.718 --> 07:49.009
- Yeah, well,
if they're homophobic,

07:49.009 --> 07:50.220
why would we even
want to live here?

07:50.220 --> 07:53.053
- Hardwood floors,
underground parking,

07:53.053 --> 07:54.354
incredible views.

07:54.354 --> 07:55.936
- Kevin?

07:55.936 --> 07:57.477
- Hey, I got to go.
- Okay.

07:57.477 --> 07:59.560
- Hi. I'm Frank.
You must be Kevin.

07:59.560 --> 08:02.863
- No, actually,
I'm his...roommate.

08:02.863 --> 08:03.864
- All right.
Well, come on in.

08:03.864 --> 08:05.776
Let's show you around.

08:12.242 --> 08:15.205
Floor to ceiling windows,
fireplace, of course.

08:15.205 --> 08:19.249
There is the second bedroom,
or study if you'd like.

08:19.249 --> 08:23.173
By the way, the kitchens here
are amazing for entertaining.

08:23.173 --> 08:26.176
And last but not least,
we have the master bedroom.

08:26.176 --> 08:28.178
- Hmm.

08:28.178 --> 08:30.891
- What a view, huh?

08:30.891 --> 08:34.935
Picture waking up to that
every single morning.

08:34.935 --> 08:37.187
Taking a shower
in the master bath.

08:37.187 --> 08:39.099
Going into the kitchen.

08:39.099 --> 08:40.520
Making pancakes.

08:40.520 --> 08:43.523
- Yeah,
I can really picture it.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.946
- Okay, I know exactly
what you're thinking.

08:45.946 --> 08:48.068
What's the catch?

08:48.068 --> 08:51.321
- (chuckles) No, that's
not what I was thinking.

08:51.321 --> 08:53.323
No, it all seems great.

08:53.323 --> 08:54.534
- And it is great.

08:54.534 --> 08:56.536
Did I mention it comes
fully furnished?

08:56.536 --> 08:57.918
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

08:57.918 --> 09:00.000
You have got to try
this Sleep Number bed.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.042
It is beyond comfortable.

09:07.588 --> 09:09.800
- Wow.

09:09.800 --> 09:12.552
(chuckles)

09:12.552 --> 09:15.345
Yeah, the thing is,
I'm not sure it's really...

09:15.345 --> 09:16.677
- What you're looking for?

09:16.677 --> 09:18.058
- Exactly.

09:18.058 --> 09:21.391
- Well,
what are you looking for?

09:21.391 --> 09:24.314
- (chuckles)

09:24.314 --> 09:26.026
That's a good question.

09:26.026 --> 09:27.487
- Well, no pressure.

09:27.487 --> 09:30.651
But just so you know,
there is a lot of interest.

09:30.651 --> 09:32.743
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

09:32.743 --> 09:34.284
The neighborhood's
really hot right now.

09:34.284 --> 09:36.406
Some great restaurants,
clubs in the area,

09:36.406 --> 09:38.619
if you like to go out.

09:38.619 --> 09:40.701
- Yeah, I do.

09:40.701 --> 09:42.332
- Well, think it over.

09:42.332 --> 09:44.544
I live in the building,
so I'm always available

09:44.544 --> 09:46.797
if you want to come back
with your roommate.

09:46.797 --> 09:49.009
- Right.

09:52.092 --> 09:53.844
Well, I should...

09:53.844 --> 09:56.596
- Yeah, sure. Well,
you have my number, so...

09:56.596 --> 09:59.019
- Yeah.

09:59.019 --> 10:01.932
- I'd love to have you
in the building.

10:08.729 --> 10:12.192
- Now, don't be disappointed
if you don't get very far.

10:12.192 --> 10:15.325
It's normal since you're doing
this way ahead of schedule.

10:15.325 --> 10:17.157
- Well, the medical director

10:17.157 --> 10:19.199
doesn't seem to think
it's too soon.

10:19.199 --> 10:22.332
- Yeah, he's got
all those degrees.

10:22.332 --> 10:24.584
I just work with people.

10:24.584 --> 10:26.957
Okay,
you are fully supported,

10:26.957 --> 10:29.009
so you don't have
to worry about falling.

10:29.009 --> 10:31.091
The harness will automatically
lock and catch you.

10:31.091 --> 10:33.423
I'm gonna be right here
beside you the whole time.

10:36.346 --> 10:38.558
You ready to take
your first step?

10:38.558 --> 10:40.310
- Hell, yes.

10:46.566 --> 10:49.399
- Okay, let's do it.

10:53.033 --> 10:54.654
Try to walk.

10:57.327 --> 10:59.489
You can do it.

11:00.831 --> 11:02.122
Does it hurt?

11:03.994 --> 11:05.245
- Want me to help
lift your foot?

11:05.245 --> 11:06.246
- No.

11:06.246 --> 11:07.587
- Just remember to breathe.

11:07.587 --> 11:11.051
Trust that
you're not gonna fall.

11:11.051 --> 11:12.592
Juliette.
- I can't breathe!

11:12.592 --> 11:14.174
I can't breathe!

11:14.174 --> 11:15.756
I can't breathe!
- It's okay.

11:15.756 --> 11:17.387
- I can't breathe!
- It's okay. You're okay.

11:17.387 --> 11:19.299
I'm gonna get your chair.

11:19.299 --> 11:22.222
- (gasping)

11:29.069 --> 11:31.691
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

11:31.691 --> 11:33.693
- You went through
something terrifying.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.155
You're still processing it.

11:35.155 --> 11:36.406
That's what flashbacks are.

11:36.406 --> 11:37.738
It's your mind
trying to protect you.

11:37.738 --> 11:42.202
- How'd you know
that's what it was?

11:42.202 --> 11:44.624
- I was in
my own kind of accident.

11:44.624 --> 11:46.326
I mean,
not exactly like yours,

11:46.326 --> 11:49.169
but I know that it's easy

11:49.169 --> 11:51.591
to get so focused
on fixing your body,

11:51.591 --> 11:53.924
you forget that your soul
needs to heal, too.

11:53.924 --> 11:56.636
- So how long
is it gonna last?

11:56.636 --> 11:59.219
When am I gonna be
back to normal?

11:59.219 --> 12:00.600
- I wish
I had a good answer.

12:00.600 --> 12:02.222
It's gonna take time.

12:04.434 --> 12:07.397
- Well, thank you
for not saying I told you so.

12:07.397 --> 12:09.850
- (laughs) You thought
I was gonna say that?

12:09.850 --> 12:17.117
- I don't know.
You seem so...tough.

12:17.117 --> 12:19.359
- I thought you seemed
pretty tough, too.

12:19.359 --> 12:22.742
Hey, you weren't ready
today, but you will be.

12:29.669 --> 12:32.292
- Oh, there he is.
Welcome to Nashville.

12:32.292 --> 12:34.254
- Thank you so much.
So cool to be here.

12:34.254 --> 12:36.176
- Yeah.
Oh, this is Deacon, Zach.

12:36.176 --> 12:37.677
- How you doing?
- Oh, my God.

12:37.677 --> 12:39.179
I cannot believe
I'm shaking hands

12:39.179 --> 12:40.760
with Deacon Claybourne.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.382
No, I feel like I know you
from your songs,

12:42.382 --> 12:44.344
although you probably
get that all the time.

12:44.344 --> 12:46.016
- 24/7.

12:46.016 --> 12:47.437
- How was your flight in?

12:47.437 --> 12:49.019
- Pretty chill.
We stopped off in Jackson Hole

12:49.019 --> 12:50.020
to surprise my cousin
for his birthday.

12:50.020 --> 12:51.441
- Oh, fun.
- Yeah.

12:51.441 --> 12:53.443
- Megan's here.
- Oh, there's the mayor.

12:53.443 --> 12:55.695
- Megan?
Hey, you look amazing.

12:55.695 --> 12:56.736
- It's so good to see you.

12:56.736 --> 12:58.398
- I'm hoping it's cool
I invited her to join us.

12:58.398 --> 12:59.900
You guys know each other,
right?

12:59.900 --> 13:01.822
- Of course. Hey.
- Good to see you guys.

13:01.822 --> 13:03.613
- You, too.
- They're starting.

13:03.613 --> 13:04.905
- How do you know Zach?

13:04.905 --> 13:06.076
- Oh, we met at a benefit.

13:06.076 --> 13:07.287
- You know,
I'm not surprised.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.578
He knows everybody.
- He really does.

13:08.578 --> 13:09.870
- It's that time.

13:09.870 --> 13:11.711
Please
put your hands together

13:11.711 --> 13:13.964
for Scarlett O'Connor
and Gunnar Scott,

13:13.964 --> 13:15.335
the Exes.

13:15.335 --> 13:17.878
- Whoo! Whoo!
(cheers and applause)

13:20.010 --> 13:21.631
- Hey, y'all.

13:21.631 --> 13:23.513
It is such a pleasure
to be here tonight.

13:23.513 --> 13:24.724
Thank you for coming.

13:24.724 --> 13:26.346
It's a real special night
for us,

13:26.346 --> 13:28.808
'cause this stage
is where we really started.

13:28.808 --> 13:31.731
And my sweet family is here.
I love you guys.

13:31.731 --> 13:33.353
So let's get to it.

13:38.818 --> 13:43.533
- ♪ Your touch, your touch
is everything now ♪

13:43.533 --> 13:51.081
♪ I feel so much,
it's taking me down, down ♪

13:51.081 --> 13:53.123
♪ Take me down ♪

13:56.166 --> 14:00.800
♪ We stand so close,
electricity ♪

14:00.800 --> 14:08.889
♪ All of you
fits so perfectly with me ♪

14:08.889 --> 14:10.730
♪ Take me now ♪

14:14.274 --> 14:18.188
♪ Your love is an earthquake
underneath my feet ♪

14:18.188 --> 14:22.362
♪ Your kiss just a taste
of everything I need ♪

