16:37.117 --> 16:39.379
Thank you, guys.
- Thank you.

16:39.379 --> 16:41.831
- Okay, look,
this might sound crazy,

16:41.831 --> 16:43.173
but I'm just gonna say it.

16:43.173 --> 16:44.754
I see an opportunity

16:44.754 --> 16:49.389
and I would like to explore it
with you, with Highway 65.

16:49.389 --> 16:51.391
- Oh.

16:51.391 --> 16:52.592
- I've reached
a point in my life

16:52.592 --> 16:54.264
where I only want to do things
that I'm passionate about,

16:54.264 --> 16:55.805
and I do not want
to waste any time.

16:55.805 --> 16:59.729
And I got this instinct
about you, the company and me,

16:59.729 --> 17:01.941
I think it could make
a good marriage.

17:01.941 --> 17:06.446
So if you are interested,
let's talk.

17:17.327 --> 17:23.163
- The guy has spent like
three hours with you total.

17:23.163 --> 17:24.164
- Well, he also says

17:24.164 --> 17:25.545
that he's been obsessed
with our music for years.

17:25.545 --> 17:27.127
He said he feels
like he knows us.

17:27.127 --> 17:29.379
- So he decides to go
in business with you

17:29.379 --> 17:31.431
just based on this feeling
he's got?

17:31.431 --> 17:33.303
That's it?
What's in it for him?

17:33.303 --> 17:36.226
- He said he wants
to do what he loves.

17:36.226 --> 17:37.597
- And that's enough?

17:37.597 --> 17:39.889
You think he got his billions
by doing what he loves?

17:39.889 --> 17:41.601
- Honey, I have no idea.

17:41.601 --> 17:44.274
I hope he did.
I would respect that.

17:44.274 --> 17:46.356
I think it's worth
hearing him out.

17:48.238 --> 17:50.240
You really didn't like him,
did you?

17:50.240 --> 17:51.821
- It's not that
I didn't like him.

17:51.821 --> 17:53.693
I mean, he's a nice enough guy
and everything.

17:53.693 --> 17:56.956
But it's just
a little weird, that's all.

17:56.956 --> 17:58.788
- I agree.
It's a little weird.

17:58.788 --> 18:01.331
I'm not even sure I want to
go into business with him.

18:01.331 --> 18:04.374
But the idea of
actually having some money

18:04.374 --> 18:05.705
for my business is exciting.

18:05.705 --> 18:06.756
- Mm-hmm.

18:09.048 --> 18:10.630
Come here.

18:14.844 --> 18:17.807
"Make a good marriage."

18:17.807 --> 18:22.182
- That was
a figure of speech.

18:22.182 --> 18:25.645
(doorbell rings)

18:28.688 --> 18:30.610
- Psst. Hey.

18:30.610 --> 18:32.111
I'm not here.

18:32.111 --> 18:33.193
- Okay.

18:34.694 --> 18:36.236
Hey.
- Hey, man.

18:36.236 --> 18:39.038
Hey, Will around?
- No. He left earlier.

18:39.038 --> 18:41.331
- Damn it. I've been trying
to reach him all day.

18:41.331 --> 18:43.413
- Yeah.

18:43.413 --> 18:47.547
(cell phone rings)

18:47.547 --> 18:48.628
- Is that his phone?

18:48.628 --> 18:51.711
- Well, maybe he is here.

18:51.711 --> 18:53.513
- Hey!

18:56.596 --> 18:58.178
- So you are alive.

18:58.178 --> 19:00.139
I texted you like 12 times.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.392
- Yeah, sorry.
My phone was dead.

19:04.894 --> 19:07.106
- So what did you think?

19:07.106 --> 19:08.898
- About what?

19:08.898 --> 19:13.233
- About the controversy
surrounding stem cell research.

19:13.233 --> 19:16.035
About the apartment.
Did you love it?

19:16.035 --> 19:18.117
- It was fine.

19:18.117 --> 19:19.449
- Just fine?

19:19.449 --> 19:21.451
- Well, I don't know.

19:21.451 --> 19:23.042
Can I get to the...

19:23.042 --> 19:24.624
- So what's wrong
with this one?

19:24.624 --> 19:26.206
- Nothing.

19:26.206 --> 19:28.628
- Clearly there's something.
- No, it was great.

19:28.628 --> 19:30.550
- Then why do you
look like that?

19:33.002 --> 19:34.924
- I woke up with a headache.

19:34.924 --> 19:37.387
- Oh, penguin.

19:39.349 --> 19:41.681
I'll start filling out
the application, okay?

19:41.681 --> 19:44.604
And then you can fill in
your part.

19:47.227 --> 19:48.568
- Cool.

19:52.732 --> 19:54.814
- Mmm.

19:54.814 --> 19:56.946
Mmm. (chuckles)

19:56.946 --> 19:59.078
- Mm-hmm.
- Best ribs in the city.

19:59.078 --> 20:00.159
- Mm-hmm.

20:00.159 --> 20:01.581
- Thank you
for meeting me here.

20:01.581 --> 20:03.493
I was starving.

20:03.493 --> 20:05.084
- Oh, yeah, of course.
I love this place.

20:05.084 --> 20:06.586
- Okay,
so I just keep thinking

20:06.586 --> 20:08.958
what you've built here
is so special,

20:08.958 --> 20:11.831
so pure of intent, the way
you put the artists first,

20:11.831 --> 20:13.002
it should be protected.

20:13.002 --> 20:15.295
And I know you're struggling

20:15.295 --> 20:17.387
like everyone else
in the industry,

20:17.387 --> 20:19.509
so here's my pitch.

20:19.509 --> 20:21.641
I lay out a certain amount
of money each year,

20:21.641 --> 20:22.842
enough to keep you afloat,

20:22.842 --> 20:24.344
to keep investing
in new artists.

20:24.344 --> 20:27.397
In exchange, I get 20%
of the company.

20:27.397 --> 20:29.349
Now, you still make
all of the decisions.

20:29.349 --> 20:30.810
I just have the right
of consultation,

20:30.810 --> 20:34.774
and I ask that you consider
the advice of my team.

20:34.774 --> 20:36.566
Which doesn't mean
that you have to take it.

20:36.566 --> 20:38.197
I mean, if this didn't work
for whatever reason,

20:38.197 --> 20:40.360
either of us could end it
with 90 days notice.

20:40.360 --> 20:41.911
Because I only want
to be in business

20:41.911 --> 20:43.783
with people who want to be
in business with me.

20:43.783 --> 20:44.914
- Good philosophy.

20:44.914 --> 20:46.576
- Yeah. That's it.

20:46.576 --> 20:49.579
If you will let me,
I think I can help Highway 65

20:49.579 --> 20:52.752
flourish in the way
it deserves to.

20:52.752 --> 20:55.004
- It's an interesting
proposition.

20:55.004 --> 20:58.177
You have a little sauce
right on the--

20:58.177 --> 21:00.930
Other side.
Yeah, yeah.

21:00.930 --> 21:03.643
- Thank you.
Yeah, see? You get it.

21:03.643 --> 21:04.644
When you have money,

21:04.644 --> 21:06.306
no one tells you when
you have sauce on your face.

21:24.664 --> 21:27.787
- Oh! Aah!

21:27.787 --> 21:30.209
- Juliette? Oh!

21:30.209 --> 21:32.712
- Oh, I'm fine.
- No, that's okay.

21:32.712 --> 21:35.084
- Don't touch me!
I can do it myself!

21:35.084 --> 21:37.377
- Okay. Okay.

21:37.377 --> 21:39.919
Here,
let me get you a pill.

21:39.919 --> 21:44.303
- No. No. No.
Avery, it's not that bad.

21:46.686 --> 21:49.098
- You haven't been
taking them, have you?

21:49.098 --> 21:51.431
- I can't.

21:51.431 --> 21:52.812
- Juliette.

21:52.812 --> 21:54.273
- I can't rely on a drug

21:54.273 --> 21:57.146
to get me through
the pain, okay?

21:57.146 --> 21:58.358
I've been through that.

21:58.358 --> 21:59.609
You want to go through that
again?

21:59.609 --> 22:00.900
You want Cadence
to go through that?

22:00.900 --> 22:02.402
- Look,
we've been through this.

22:02.402 --> 22:04.283
The doctor said as long as
your dosage is monitored--

22:04.283 --> 22:06.245
- Yeah, that's easy
for her to say.

22:06.245 --> 22:08.748
I'm the one
who has to live with myself.

22:08.748 --> 22:12.832
You have no idea what it's like
to want to escape,

22:12.832 --> 22:14.834
to be so tempted
to take them.

22:14.834 --> 22:17.166
- Look,
I know it's not easy,

22:17.166 --> 22:19.669
but I also know
that you can't get better

22:19.669 --> 22:20.960
unless you take what
the doctor prescribed you.

22:20.960 --> 22:23.423
- It's my decision, okay?

22:23.423 --> 22:26.095
I might not be able to do
anything for myself,

22:26.095 --> 22:28.598
but I sure as hell can keep
myself off those pills!

22:28.598 --> 22:30.890
- Listen,
I am trying to help you.

22:30.890 --> 22:33.102
- Stop! Stop helping!

22:33.102 --> 22:36.105
It makes me--
I hate it!

22:36.105 --> 22:38.778
And we both know
you don't want to do it!

22:38.778 --> 22:39.979
- What?

22:39.979 --> 22:42.071
- Oh, come on!
Just admit it!

22:42.071 --> 22:43.613
You feel obligated!

22:43.613 --> 22:44.944
Like it's your job
to take care of me!

22:44.944 --> 22:46.035
- What are you
talking about?

22:46.035 --> 22:47.447
That is not how I feel!

22:47.447 --> 22:48.868
- That's how anyone
would feel!

22:48.868 --> 22:50.910
- God, you are such
a pain in the ass!

22:50.910 --> 22:52.161
You know that?
And don't worry.

22:52.161 --> 22:53.793
It has nothing to do
with you being hurt.

22:53.793 --> 22:56.165
Because you've been like this
since the day I met you.

22:56.165 --> 22:57.707
You just push people away,

22:57.707 --> 23:00.259
because God forbid
you might ever need anyone!

23:13.973 --> 23:16.065
- What?

23:16.065 --> 23:17.777
The listing went down.

23:17.777 --> 23:19.899
They must have given it
to someone else.

23:19.899 --> 23:21.400
- Oh.

23:21.400 --> 23:22.732
- How did we not get it?

23:22.732 --> 23:24.694
You sent the application
Monday, right?

23:24.694 --> 23:26.155
- Yeah.

23:26.155 --> 23:27.657
- Damn.

23:27.657 --> 23:31.621
- You know, that place
wasn't that great anyway.

23:31.621 --> 23:33.623
The bathroom was cramped,

23:33.623 --> 23:37.126
and the kitchen
kind of had a weird smell.

23:37.126 --> 23:38.458
Did you notice that?

23:38.458 --> 23:42.001
- No. I thought
it was pretty perfect.

23:42.001 --> 23:44.253
- Sorry.

23:44.253 --> 23:45.925
- Yeah,
I'm just disappointed.

23:45.925 --> 23:47.426
- I know.

23:47.426 --> 23:51.180
- Well, back to Craigslist.

23:59.058 --> 24:01.360
- You don't have to come in
with me.

24:01.360 --> 24:03.362
- No, it's no big deal,
really.

24:03.362 --> 24:05.945
- No. I mean,
I don't want you to.

24:05.945 --> 24:07.406
- Oh.

24:07.406 --> 24:10.780
- I'm sorry. I just
got to do this by myself.

24:41.771 --> 24:44.774
- Well, hello.

24:44.774 --> 24:46.946
Sorry to interrupt.

24:46.946 --> 24:48.447
I just wanted you to know

24:48.447 --> 24:52.031
that I was here just in case
you'd like to talk.

24:52.031 --> 24:53.282
- Okay.

24:55.535 --> 24:57.827
Wait.

25:00.540 --> 25:02.381
Actually, never mind.

25:02.381 --> 25:05.044
- Well, you might as well ask
just what you want to ask.

25:05.044 --> 25:06.465
It's what I'm here for.

25:06.465 --> 25:08.628
- (sighs)

25:08.628 --> 25:10.630
I hardly ever do this.

25:10.630 --> 25:12.892
- Do what?

25:12.892 --> 25:14.473
- Pray.

25:14.473 --> 25:17.727
- You want to pray?

25:17.727 --> 25:23.022
- Yeah,
but I don't know how to.

25:23.022 --> 25:25.815
- There's no way how,
no one way.

25:25.815 --> 25:31.030
It's just a conversation
between you and God.

25:31.030 --> 25:34.413
- How do I start?
What am I supposed to do?

25:34.413 --> 25:37.456
- There's nothing to do.

25:37.456 --> 25:39.328
Just say what you feel.

25:55.054 --> 25:57.977
- I just have one question.

26:03.983 --> 26:06.065
Why me?

26:09.859 --> 26:14.784
Why me and not the other people
on that plane?

26:14.784 --> 26:18.077
It's not 'cause
I'm a better person.

26:20.750 --> 26:22.662
I don't understand.

26:27.206 --> 26:29.258
I'm lost.

26:31.971 --> 26:35.765
Help me, please?

27:03.582 --> 27:08.337
(cell phone rings)

27:11.380 --> 27:13.342
- Hello?

27:13.342 --> 27:15.464
- Rayna.
Hey, it's Zach Welles.

27:15.464 --> 27:17.757
- Oh, hey, Zach.

27:17.757 --> 27:19.849
- Listen, it just hit me.

27:19.849 --> 27:22.561
I got the perfect director
for you: Damien George.

27:22.561 --> 27:23.933
- Damien George?

27:23.933 --> 27:26.185
- Yeah, his movie with
J-Law just fell apart.

27:26.185 --> 27:27.436
- I don't think
Damien George

27:27.436 --> 27:29.398
is gonna want to do
a music video, Zach.

27:29.398 --> 27:31.230
- You have no idea
the favor this guy owes me.

27:31.230 --> 27:32.441
He was two weeks into shooting
"Night Dogs"

27:32.441 --> 27:33.693
when the bond company--

27:33.693 --> 27:35.234
- Look, that's
so generous of you,

27:35.234 --> 27:36.655
but I just think--

27:36.655 --> 27:38.657
- No, seriously, they
were gonna shut him down.

27:38.657 --> 27:40.159
I mean, they came to set--

27:40.159 --> 27:41.991
- I just think we have to
slow it down a little bit.

27:41.991 --> 27:45.204
I mean, I'm still considering
your proposition.

27:45.204 --> 27:48.047
- Right, of course you are.

27:48.047 --> 27:50.459
Sorry. This is what happens
when I get excited.

27:50.459 --> 27:51.751
I get ahead of myself.

27:51.751 --> 27:53.092
Hey, listen,
I want you to know

27:53.092 --> 27:55.294
I'm honestly not trying
to pressure you

27:55.294 --> 27:57.426
or influence
your decision in any way.

27:57.426 --> 27:59.428
I respect you too much
for that crap.

27:59.428 --> 28:00.850
- Well, I appreciate it.

28:00.850 --> 28:02.681
- Yeah,
and this Damien thing,

28:02.681 --> 28:05.014
it has nothing to do
with our deal

28:05.014 --> 28:06.856
or lack thereof.

28:06.856 --> 28:08.858
You could say no right now
and I'd be totally willing

28:08.858 --> 28:11.440
to hook you up with Damien
no strings attached.

28:11.440 --> 28:14.233
- Thank you. Well, I'm gonna
keep thinking about all of it.

28:14.233 --> 28:16.405
And you have a good time,

28:16.405 --> 28:18.117
and I'll see you
when you get back here.

28:18.117 --> 28:19.448
- Sweet. See you later.

28:19.448 --> 28:20.740
- Bye.

28:23.743 --> 28:25.534
- What's all this?

28:25.534 --> 28:27.206
- I don't know.

28:31.250 --> 28:32.331
- (sighs)

28:37.676 --> 28:40.299
- Wow.

28:40.299 --> 28:43.102
It's been a while
since we got one of these.

28:43.102 --> 28:45.684
You remember that woman
who sent you her socks?

28:45.684 --> 28:48.147
Sure was easy to keep
your address private

28:48.147 --> 28:49.398
before the internet.

28:49.398 --> 28:50.519
- Well, this didn't even
come through the mail.

28:50.519 --> 28:51.650
It didn't have a stamp on it
or anything.

28:51.650 --> 28:52.982
- Which means
they were here.

28:52.982 --> 28:54.273
- I don't know.

28:54.273 --> 28:56.235
This stuff
makes me nervous these days.

28:56.235 --> 28:58.407
- I know. I mean,
chances are he's harmless,

28:58.407 --> 29:00.029
but if it makes you
feel better,

29:00.029 --> 29:01.991
you might want to beef up your
home security just in case.

29:01.991 --> 29:04.163
I mean, I don't think you
should lose any sleep over it.

29:04.163 --> 29:06.745
Better to lose sleep

29:06.745 --> 29:08.287
over what's gonna happen
with the label.

29:08.287 --> 29:09.999
- Nice.

29:09.999 --> 29:12.541
- Don't worry. I'm losing sleep
over that too, Bucky.

29:12.541 --> 29:14.173
- Any closer
to making a decision?

29:14.173 --> 29:15.835
- Oh, I don't know.

29:15.835 --> 29:17.877
I just can't help but think
this whole thing with Zach

29:17.877 --> 29:19.718
is just too good to be true.

29:19.718 --> 29:21.971
- Yeah, well, sometimes those
things turn out to be true.

29:21.971 --> 29:23.222
You did.

29:23.222 --> 29:25.554
- What? You think
I should do it now?

29:25.554 --> 29:27.226
- Well, I was listening
to him on the phone,

29:27.226 --> 29:29.648
and I started thinking maybe
this is right, you know.

29:29.648 --> 29:32.231
Maybe we should just
accept our good fortune.

29:32.231 --> 29:34.023
- Just not before
we talk to Sheila, though.

29:34.023 --> 29:35.734
- Oh, of course, I'm gonna have
a lawyer look at the contract.

29:35.734 --> 29:37.736
I have a feeling she'll find
a million loopholes

29:37.736 --> 29:39.358
that are just gonna
screw us over.

29:39.358 --> 29:41.160
- What if she doesn't?

29:41.160 --> 29:42.571
- Well, if she doesn't,

29:42.571 --> 29:44.533
then we're just gonna
have to make damn sure

29:44.533 --> 29:47.456
that Zach and I want
the same thing for the label.

29:47.456 --> 29:50.409
- It sure would help us
make this album of ours.

29:58.337 --> 30:00.549
- It's a visual love letter

30:00.549 --> 30:03.342
to a woman
so electric and alive,

30:03.342 --> 30:04.924
she can't be contained.

30:04.924 --> 30:07.847
She's messy,
she's passionate.

30:07.847 --> 30:09.558
She's feeling
everything at once.

30:09.558 --> 30:12.021
- You got all that
from the song?

30:12.021 --> 30:13.893
- The song's just
the jumping off point.

30:13.893 --> 30:15.314
It's like a dream.

30:15.314 --> 30:18.027
I'm seeing
this wild creature

30:18.027 --> 30:19.528
who doesn't know
how to be in the world,

30:19.528 --> 30:21.360
and the man who loves her,

30:21.360 --> 30:23.532
who wants to hold onto her,
but can't.

30:23.532 --> 30:26.785
And it's set in one of those
grand sweeping mansions,

30:26.785 --> 30:31.160
this sort of backdrop
of old world propriety.

30:42.631 --> 30:44.263
- I'm a terrible person.

30:44.263 --> 30:45.764
- No, you're not.

30:45.764 --> 30:47.176
- Well,
you have to say that

30:47.176 --> 30:48.387
'cause you're my friend.

30:48.387 --> 30:49.728
- You did the right thing
in a way.

30:49.728 --> 30:51.971
I mean, you knew
if you stayed in that place,

30:51.971 --> 30:53.933
you'd always be tempted.

30:53.933 --> 30:55.644
- Yeah, but it's not
just that guy.

30:55.644 --> 30:58.737
It's guys on the street,
at my gigs,

30:58.737 --> 31:00.479
at the ATM just now.

31:00.479 --> 31:02.111
- Being tempted
isn't the same thing

31:02.111 --> 31:03.532
as following through
with it.

31:03.532 --> 31:06.195
- Yeah, but I can't
stop thinking about it.

31:06.195 --> 31:08.367
I keep thinking

31:08.367 --> 31:11.620
what would life be like
with someone else?

31:11.620 --> 31:13.082
- Sounds like you have FOMO.

31:13.082 --> 31:14.914
- What'd you call me?

31:14.914 --> 31:17.456
- Oh, FOMO.

31:17.456 --> 31:19.758
Fear of Missing Out.

31:19.758 --> 31:21.050
- (laughs) Oh.

31:21.050 --> 31:22.671
- Which makes sense.

31:22.671 --> 31:25.004
You know, he's your first
real relationship.

31:25.004 --> 31:26.425
It's not like you been
with a lot of dudes.

31:26.425 --> 31:28.347
- Yeah, but I never
even cared about that.

31:28.347 --> 31:31.010
All I wanted
was to be with him.

31:31.010 --> 31:33.602
He does this thing

31:33.602 --> 31:37.356
we saw in a documentary
about penguins.

31:37.356 --> 31:40.279
They touch foreheads.

31:40.279 --> 31:42.731
That's how they kiss.

31:42.731 --> 31:45.154
- That's nauseating.

31:45.154 --> 31:46.986
- Yeah, I know.

31:49.328 --> 31:51.660
I just gotta focus
on what's real.

31:51.660 --> 31:53.032
Me and him.

31:53.032 --> 31:55.534
You know,
once we're living together

31:55.534 --> 31:57.246
and we're with each other
every day,

31:57.246 --> 31:58.837
it's gonna be different.

31:58.837 --> 32:00.539
- Will, listen,

32:00.539 --> 32:03.422
I can't tell you
if you should stay with Kevin,

32:03.422 --> 32:06.135
but I can tell you that never
in the history of the world

32:06.135 --> 32:09.008
has moving in together
made things easier.

32:09.008 --> 32:11.470
Believe me,
it only gets harder.

32:11.470 --> 32:14.433
And if you love the person,
then it's worth it.

32:14.433 --> 32:19.228
But it will test you more
than you ever thought possible.

32:19.228 --> 32:21.480
- I'm such an ass
going on about this.

32:21.480 --> 32:22.941
You got real problems.

32:22.941 --> 32:24.063
- Well, I didn't
come out tonight

32:24.063 --> 32:25.234
to talk about my problems.

32:25.234 --> 32:26.775
Yours
are a welcome distraction.

32:26.775 --> 32:28.237
- I just don't know
if it's normal

32:28.237 --> 32:32.201
or if it means
something more,

32:32.201 --> 32:37.206
like...maybe we're not
meant to be together.

32:37.206 --> 32:39.538
- You got to figure out
what you want.

32:39.538 --> 32:41.960
I mean,
what you actually want,

32:41.960 --> 32:43.422
not what
you think you should.

32:45.084 --> 32:48.137
(pinball machine dings)

32:54.093 --> 32:55.514
- [Man on TV]
If you'd like to add

32:55.514 --> 32:58.017
more of Nick's recipes
in culinary adventures

32:58.017 --> 33:00.269
to your collection,
now you can.

33:00.269 --> 33:02.441
It's just this easy.

33:02.441 --> 33:05.404
The companion cookbook to
"Cooking With Nick Stellino"

33:05.404 --> 33:09.238
is available for 34.95
plus shipping and handling.

33:09.238 --> 33:12.241
The two disk DVD set
of the complete series

33:12.241 --> 33:13.492
and the CD-Rom of recipes...

33:13.492 --> 33:15.914
- Buy one now,
you get a bonus gift.

33:15.914 --> 33:18.747
- Don't tempt me.

33:18.747 --> 33:20.919
(turns off TV)

33:20.919 --> 33:22.921
The other day--
- Listen, Juliette--

33:22.921 --> 33:24.002
Oh, I'm sorry.

33:24.002 --> 33:25.884
- No, you go.

33:25.884 --> 33:28.927
- I'm just sorry.

33:28.927 --> 33:30.929
I shouldn't
have yelled like that.

33:30.929 --> 33:34.133
- You were right about me,

33:34.133 --> 33:39.598
about why I hate
being like this, helpless.

33:39.598 --> 33:41.560
- You're not helpless.
- You know what I mean.

33:41.560 --> 33:45.944
I don't want to need you,
but I do.

33:45.944 --> 33:47.276
I always have.

33:47.276 --> 33:49.608
- Come here.

33:53.862 --> 33:55.454
- I'm just so scared

33:55.454 --> 33:57.456
you're gonna start to feel
like I'm this burden.

33:57.456 --> 33:59.658
- No, never.

33:59.658 --> 34:01.290
I could never feel that way.

34:01.290 --> 34:02.581
You got to know that.

34:02.581 --> 34:04.123
- So I took it out on you.

34:04.123 --> 34:05.544
- It's okay.
- I'm sorry.

34:05.544 --> 34:07.546
I'm sorry that I lied to you
about the pills.

34:07.546 --> 34:10.879
- It's okay.
I know how hard it's been.

34:10.879 --> 34:14.263
I mean, I don't know.
I can only imagine.

34:14.263 --> 34:17.226
- It's been harder on you.
- What?

34:17.226 --> 34:20.769
- You're the one
who has to do everything.

34:20.769 --> 34:25.184
Feed me, make my appointments,
take care of the baby.

34:25.184 --> 34:27.816
- Juliette, I want to.

34:27.816 --> 34:30.989
- You do?

34:30.989 --> 34:32.451
- Yes.

34:41.830 --> 34:44.002
Whoa.

34:44.002 --> 34:45.914
Your arms
are getting strong.

34:45.914 --> 34:48.667
- One of the perks
of physical therapy.

34:48.667 --> 34:51.670
- You sure
you want to do this?

34:51.670 --> 34:53.091
- Yes.

34:56.595 --> 35:00.599
- I just...
I don't want to hurt you.

35:00.599 --> 35:02.311
- You won't.

35:09.858 --> 35:11.530
- Wait, wait.

35:11.530 --> 35:12.941
- Oh, I knew it.

35:12.941 --> 35:14.653
- No, it's not
what you think.

35:14.653 --> 35:16.074
- I'm just this broken thing

35:16.074 --> 35:17.946
that you're too afraid
to even touch.

35:17.946 --> 35:21.290
- You are the most beautiful
woman in the world to me.

35:21.290 --> 35:23.202
- Then what is it?

35:23.202 --> 35:24.873
- It's stupid.

35:24.873 --> 35:26.004
- Tell me.

35:26.004 --> 35:27.456
- (sighs)

35:30.249 --> 35:34.092
I just...

35:34.092 --> 35:37.306
I feel...

35:37.306 --> 35:43.101
It's like with everything
that happened with us...

35:43.101 --> 35:44.263
- Oh, my God.

35:44.263 --> 35:45.764
- It's okay.

35:45.764 --> 35:47.646
- I never wanted
to hurt you.

35:47.646 --> 35:52.070
- I wouldn't trade it,
not for a second.

35:54.533 --> 35:59.077
I don't think you have any idea
how much I love you.

36:01.830 --> 36:03.242
But I just--

36:03.242 --> 36:04.743
- You need time.

36:07.706 --> 36:08.957
- Yeah.

36:20.719 --> 36:23.181
- It's a pretty
straightforward contract.

36:23.181 --> 36:24.513
No surprises I can see.

36:24.513 --> 36:25.854
There's an escape clause

36:25.854 --> 36:27.726
that protects you
if you want to get out.

36:27.726 --> 36:30.399
There's no such thing
as free money,

36:30.399 --> 36:34.022
but this is about
as close as it gets.

36:39.027 --> 36:42.531
- You are cordially invited
to a loud club

36:42.531 --> 36:44.082
to come see
your boyfriend play.

36:53.592 --> 36:55.384
What's wrong?

36:57.836 --> 36:59.548
- I found this in the trash.

37:01.840 --> 37:04.343
You never sent it.

37:04.343 --> 37:06.014
- I didn't know what to do.

37:06.014 --> 37:09.898
I didn't...I didn't know
how to tell you.

37:09.898 --> 37:11.059
- Tell me what?

37:14.022 --> 37:16.234
There's someone else.

37:16.234 --> 37:17.736
- No.

37:17.736 --> 37:19.117
- It's so obvious.
- No, that's not it.

37:19.117 --> 37:20.409
- How can I believe you?

37:20.409 --> 37:21.950
You know how much
I wanted that apartment.

37:21.950 --> 37:24.533
- Look, you have every right
to hate me.

37:24.533 --> 37:28.457
I can't even explain why.
I just...

37:28.457 --> 37:32.250
- What? Just be real
with me, Will.

37:32.250 --> 37:33.542
- I don't...

37:36.254 --> 37:38.797
I don't want
to live with you.

37:42.551 --> 37:44.262
- This was your idea.

37:44.262 --> 37:45.644
- I know.

37:45.644 --> 37:47.886
- How long
have you felt this way?

37:47.886 --> 37:48.977
- A while, I guess.
I don't know.

37:48.977 --> 37:51.940
I didn't want it to be true.

37:51.940 --> 37:53.982
- Well,
I thought we were fine.

37:53.982 --> 37:56.655
I thought you were happy.
- I am.

37:56.655 --> 38:02.451
I just feel like
I need a little space or...

38:02.451 --> 38:04.282
- Are you breaking up with me?
- No.

38:04.282 --> 38:07.075
- It sure as hell feels like it.
- No, no, Kevin, Kevin.

38:07.075 --> 38:10.539
- If I hadn't found that
application in the trash,

38:10.539 --> 38:13.041
would you have told me
any of this?

38:18.417 --> 38:20.799
- I was trying
to find the right way.

38:20.799 --> 38:25.764
- You know, I had a feeling
from the beginning

38:25.764 --> 38:28.427
that you weren't ready
for a real relationship.

38:28.427 --> 38:31.890
I should have
trusted my gut.

38:31.890 --> 38:33.812
This isn't about
just moving in.

38:33.812 --> 38:37.315
This is the whole thing,
isn't it?

38:47.366 --> 38:49.207
- I'm sorry.

38:52.120 --> 38:54.953
[Emcee] All right. Y'all
having a good time tonight?

38:54.953 --> 38:58.377
Ha ha. All right,
let's keep things going.

38:58.377 --> 39:01.129
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the stage

39:01.129 --> 39:04.092
Will Lexington!

39:04.092 --> 39:06.224
(cheers and applause)

39:09.598 --> 39:12.180
(band plays upbeat music)

39:13.812 --> 39:14.933
- All right!

39:30.909 --> 39:34.292
(band stops playing)

39:40.208 --> 39:44.302
I'm sorry. I guess I'm just
not feeling that one tonight.

39:54.012 --> 39:57.436
I, uh...
I'd like to play you a song

39:57.436 --> 40:02.731
that I wrote with someone
real special,

40:02.731 --> 40:04.282
my first love.

